            The whisky industry was deeply disappointed because it was hoping for a reduction in duty. The duty has been pegged, but when one considers the amount of income that can be generated, the Government seem in danger of killing the goose that lays the golden egg&#x2014;or at least of not encouraging the goose to lay the golden egg. That is an example of poor fiscal management.
          </p>
